        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 6:42AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 642 AM CDT/542 AM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Blackfoot to near Swan
Creek Rec Area to 8 miles northeast of Whitlocks Bay Rec Area.
Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Akaska, Lowry, New Everets Resort, Swan Creek Rec Area, Blackfoot,
and Lake Oahe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
